narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned the correct process of writing an essay. In class, I soaked up the techniques and strategies that one should take to write an effective essay.

I learned a dynamic understanding of what home means to both individuals and community. I improved in close-reading and critical analysis in multiple mediums, a workflow of organizing papers, and working with sources in ways relevant to academic discussions.
I learned how expand my thinking to reach a central idea

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The strengths of the class were the assignments and the way in which they were all aligned. The smaller assignments leading up made the bigger overall assignments easier. I dont recall many weaknesses of this class.
This course is very good, and the professor is flexible with due dates as long as you communicate with her ahead of time

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, this course will develop your writing skills more than they already are.
Yes, if you're interested in improving your writing skills (in the editing process, working with sources, discussing with others) and concepts of home, this course is a rigorous but well-worth class.
Yes, you learn basic necessities when writing papers
